    "analysis": "We have completed metric-level anomaly detection and a broad trace-level scan. Key findings so far: (1) Metrics show notable anomalies in currencyservice (CPU spikes and small latency increases around 12:44–12:46 UTC), emailservice (small memory excursions ~12:43 UTC), and workload spikes in productcatalogservice and recommendationservice (~12:45 UTC). (2) A global trace summary indicated elevated frontend->checkoutservice duration p95 (~3.97s) in the full series, but the earlier trace scan returned only constant zero error_rate traces (error_rate instrumentation appears constant-zero and not useful). Given multiple candidate faulty services remain, we must use trace duration and row_count features to localize which service is the most downstream faulty service in call chains and whether checkoutservice latency spike is present in the incident window. Therefore the next step is a focused trace analysis on checkoutservice and currencyservice (the strongest metric candidates), computing global thresholds (P95/P5) and then checking the incident window for duration/row_count anomalies and earliest occurrence times. This will tell us whether checkoutservice duration spikes occurred in the incident window and whether currencyservice trace features show correlated anomalies.",
